    "What is software development?",
    "Software development is the process of creating computer programs or applications. It involves designing, coding, testing, and maintaining software systems to meet specific user needs or solve particular problems.",
    "What skills are important for a career in software development?",
    "A career in software development requires a combination of technical and non-technical skills. Technical skills include programming languages (such as Java, Python, or C++), database management, software testing, and version control. Non-technical skills like problem-solving, critical thinking, teamwork, and effective communication are also essential.",
